node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we spoke to @bimmawilliams, co-founder and host of the @claimastories podcast. Claima — ”claima” as in “claim a seat at the table” — is a podcast with a mission: to give young BIPOC creatives the inspiration, and roadmap, they need to make good on their ambitions. Bimma joins us from the road — specifically from, a custom-rigged 1993 Mitsubishi Delica Starwagon rechristened as “Storytella,” his mobile podcast studio during a 30-day, four-city tour of the West Coast. Here, he gives his best advice for young BIPOC creatives looking for professional advancement and shares a few of the stories that have moved him most. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.title: DMTV Milkshake: Making Space for BIPOC Creatives

🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

Featuring a vessel from @angusandceleste! \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we spoke to @bimmawilliams, co-founder and host of the @claimastories podcast. Claima — ”claima” as in “claim a seat at the table” — is a podcast with a mission: to give young BIPOC creatives the inspiration, and roadmap, they need to make good on their ambitions. Bimma joins us from the road — specifically from, a custom-rigged 1993 Mitsubishi Delica Starwagon rechristened as “Storytella,” his mobile podcast studio during a 30-day, four-city tour of the West Coast. Here, he gives his best advice for young BIPOC creatives looking for professional advancement and shares a few of the stories that have moved him most. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.text: It’s fair to say that corded headphones have followed a similar trajectory as manual transmissions: an arc trending ever downward. But just as auto enthusiasts still regale the pleasures of shifting gears manually, so too will an audiophile defend the merits of plugging in when it comes to experiencing your favorite music over headphones. And while the aesthetics over your ears won't improve the quality of the sound pumping into them, it surely helps makes the case for the cord. \\\ At the link in bio, read about the painstakingly crafted Meze 99 Classics over-the-ear headphones that bring warmth to your listening (in more ways than one). 🔗

node.text: Modern home wi-fi systems have done an admirable job of disguising their tech in unassuming and non-intrusive housings, designed to blend in to your home while still delivering the connectivity that you need and expect. It’s the same impetus which inspired British industrial product designers Hans Ramzan and Alex Fleming to take a stab at domesticating wi-fi within the home with their own proposed concept, FIVE. "Our mission," says Ramzan, "puts people before technology, humanizing the domestic Wi-Fi system to create the world’s first smart 5G router for the home.” \\\ Read more about FIVE at the link in bio. 🔗

The process of designing the Burnt Cork collection, an homage to the mountainous areas of Pedrógão Grande that were devastated by forest fires, began in October 2018 when @noeduchaufourlawrance visited a small family-owned cork production facility, NF Cork, in Faro. During the tour, Duchaufour-Lawrance noticed a pile of discarded burnt cork and everything clicked. From there, he sketched a series of furniture pieces and Burnt Cork became Duchaufour-Lawrance and the @madeinsitu team’s second collection. \\\ Read more about the Burnt Cork Collection at the link in bio. 🔗
